# CODEOWNERS for earshot-tools/earshot.
#
# AI sessions (Claude Code) commit as stivoo-bot. CODEOWNERS ensures the
# repo owner (@inoyatov) reviews PRs that touch critical files. With
# require_code_owner_reviews: true in branch protection, the bot cannot
# merge PRs touching these files without owner approval.
#
# No default catch-all — only explicitly listed paths require owner
# review. This lets the bot merge PRs touching unlisted files without
# approval (e.g., source code under plugin/src/) while still gating
# every change that could weaken enforcement.
#
# Mirrors the asal-world CODEOWNERS pattern. See docs/decisions/engineering/.

# ── Gate files (quality + security infrastructure) ───
# These control CI gates, linting, branch protection, and security policy.
# Changes here can silently weaken enforcement. The bot CANNOT self-approve.
